snippet.textDisplay:
Total Deaths US :: 1979
Total Recovered US :: 3224
Total :: 5201. 1979/5201 = 38% mortality rate.
(Total Cases :: 118,590)
(March 14th(14 days), 3600 cases. March 17th(11 days) - 6000 cases. Fits in line)


World::
Total Deaths :: 30,361
Total Recovered :: 139,591
Total :: 169,952. 30361/169,952 = 17.86% Mortality.
(Total Cases :: 654,046)
If we look back to March 14th(14 days), there was 136,000 cases. March 17th(11 days) - 200,000 cases. Also fits in line.)


You have to look back two weeks to compare deaths to cases reported now. NY reports average time on ventilator = 11-17 days. So go back 2 weeks and look at coronavirus cases, and then look at deaths reported today. And you see real mortality rate.
So in 2 weeks (April 11th), judging by world cases, there will be about 111,187 deaths (17%) And US will have about 20,160 (17%).


Now you might ask, why is U.S. cases mortality currently 38%? Because we werent testing everyone back then. So we only found severe cases that people ended up in hospital for. So out of severe cases that ended up in hospital, about 38% of those die.
